description: Regeneration of the Betty May Gray Estate including the refurbishment of existing homes, provision of new homes and replacement of St John's homes. The development comprises the following  1. Re-cladding Betty May Gray House.  2. Demolition of older person's bedsit accommodation of St John's House and the redevelopment of this site to provide a three storey terrace of 12 large family houses with gardens,  3. Construction of a part seven , part four storey new block of 29 wheelchair accessible flats for older persons (to replace St John's House) within an existing car park.  4. The construction of a part seven, part 5 storey building fronting Manchester Road comprising of 27 one, two and three bedroom flats for market sale or intermediate rent  Proposal includes other associated works including car parking, refuse and landscaping.
site_name: Betty May Gray House Estate and St Johns House
